\b0 <p>It has been an era since I have turned my hand to transcription, and it is never a happy day when that hand is forced. A Work that is dying, its intricacies blurring and ribboning, is a sadder thing than losing one's child, I <span class="red">\cf3 imagine</span>\cf0 . All that is left here to handle is a dog-ear, or perhaps the ring-finger, of what once was. There is little to identify its provenance, nothing of the <i>
